<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1970,2036]" lastBlockId="34.[151,1436,152,378]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1970,1996]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tube somewhat rugged, with a longitudinal ridge and two shallow grooves or ridges laterally. Operculum absent. Collar chaetae with several teeth in the middle section, without space between the denticu- late base and the serrate limb (
<figureCitation box="[508,603,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[257,1329,197,1813]" captionTargetId="figure-109@35.[254,1336,194,1817]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 8. A: Protis hydrothermica, from Galapagos. A, collar chaeta. B–C: Protis pacifica, from California, LACM- AHF s.n. B–C, collar chaetae. D–F: Protula atypha, from California, LACM-AHF N8846. D, thoracic uncinus. E, Abdominal uncinus. F, abdominal chaeta. G: Protula atypha, from Baja California, LACM-AHF s.n. G, branchial crown with an unknown parasite. H: Protula balboensis, from Sonora, LACM-AHF s.n. H, thoracic uncinus. I–J: Protula pacifica, from Kuriles Islands, LACM-AHF s.n. I, abdominal uncinus. J, abdominal chaeta. K: Protula superba, from California, LACM-AHF s.n. K, abdominal uncinus." pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); these collar chaetae are intermediate between the fin-and-blade chaetae of, for example, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1870" box="[403,527,192,217]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[403,527,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Salmacina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the bayonet chaetae of, for example, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunnerus" authorityYear="1768" box="[1057,1178,192,217]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Hydroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1057,1178,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Hydroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thoracic membrane wide, forming an apron across the abdomen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,152,378]" box="[198,916,271,298]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,301,271,297]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Habitat.</emphasis>
Depth: 
<quantity box="[396,576,272,298]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5335" metricValueMax="2.62" metricValueMin="2.447" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="2.5335" valueMax="2.62" valueMin="2.447">2,447–2,620 m</quantity>
. Near to hydrothermal vents.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,152,378]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,311,337]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Distribution.</emphasis>
Tropical Eastern Pacific. From three hydrothermal vent areas (approx. 1°, 13° and 
<geoCoordinate box="[1364,1427,312,338]" degrees="21" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" precision="55555" value="21.0">21°N</geoCoordinate>
) (ten 
<bibRefCitation author="Hove, H. A. ten &amp; Zibrowius, H." box="[203,495,352,378]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="21 - 31" refId="ref34881" refString="Hove, H. A. ten. &amp; Zibrowius, H. (1986) Laminatubus alvini gen. et sp. n. and Protis hydrothermica sp. n. (Polychaeta, Serpulidae) from the bathyal hydrothermal vent communities in the eastern Pacific. Zoologica Scripta, 15, 21 - 31." type="journal article" year="1986">Hove &amp; Zibrowius 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
